<reference id="class_rendereroptions">
    <title><ph keyref="RendererOptions" /></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc">Video renderer options.</ph></shortdesc>
    <refbody>
        <section id="prototype">
            <p outputclass="codeblock">
            <codeblock props="android" outputclass="language-java" />
            <codeblock props="ios mac" outputclass="language-objectivec" />
            <codeblock props="cpp" outputclass="language-cpp" />
            <codeblock props="electron" outputclass="language-typescript">export interface RendererOptions {
                    append: boolean;
                    contentMode: CONTENT_MODE;
                    mirror: boolean;
                    }</codeblock>
            <codeblock props="cs" outputclass="language-csharp" />
            <codeblock props="rn" outputclass="language-typescript" />
            <codeblock props="flutter" outputclass="language-dart" /> </p>
        </section>
        <section id="parameters">
            <title><text conref="../conref/conref_api_metadata.dita#conref_api_metadata/property" /></title>
            <parml>
            <plentry>
                <pt>append</pt>
                <pd>When the new video is connected to the DOM, whether to use the native <apiname>appendChild</apiname> method to add a child DOM:
                    <ul>
                    <li><codeph><ph keyref="true" /></codeph>: Add a child DOM. The new video can be played together with the original video.</li>
                    <li><codeph><ph keyref="false" /></codeph>: (Default) Do not add a child DOM. Only play the new video.</li>
                    </ul></pd>
            </plentry>
            <plentry>
                <pt>contentMode</pt>
                <pd>Video display modes. See <xref href="enum_contentmode.dita" />.</pd>
            </plentry>
            <plentry>
                <pt>mirror</pt>
                <pd>Whether to enable mirror mode when rendering video:
                    <ul>
                    <li><codeph><ph keyref="true" /></codeph>: Enable mirror mode.</li>
                    <li><codeph><ph keyref="false" /></codeph>: (Default) Do not enable mirror mode.</li>
                    </ul></pd>
            </plentry>
            </parml> </section>
    </refbody>
